\b How to register a call sign as a new user on DSTAR\b0\par
\par
Before you can talk on any of the reflectors (anything other than the local repeater) you must register your call sign.  \par
\par
Since Paulding ARES now owns repeaters we have the ability to register call signs.  Anyone who needs to register can go to {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://wx4pca.dstargateway.org }}{\fldrslt{https://wx4pca.dstargateway.org\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20  and click the registration link at the top left.  An admin (currently Dan W4DTO) will be notified when someone requests registration and can finish up the process. \par
\par
  \par
\par
1)      The VHF repeater will normally stay linked to REF030B so that we are linked to the other DSTAR repeaters in Georgia.  Browse to {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK http://www.dstarinfo.com/repeater-maps.aspx }}{\fldrslt{http://www.dstarinfo.com/repeater-maps.aspx\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20  to see a list of all of the DSTAR repeaters in Georgia (or in the world!).\par
\par
2)      Feel free to link and unlink the repeater at any time.  Listen first and announce your intention to be sure no one is using the repeater.  But, then link at will.   There is a list of all of the D-PLUS reflectors at {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK http://www.dstarinfo.com/reflectors.aspx }}{\fldrslt{http://www.dstarinfo.com/reflectors.aspx\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20 .   You can create commands in your radio to link to any of these.  Read over the list when you have a chance.  Some pretty interesting reflectors out there.\par
\par
3)      If you link the repeater, drop the link when you are finished and link back to REF030B.  The system will be configured to drop links and return to REF030B after a few minutes of inactivity in case someone forgets to drop the link.\par
\par
4)      Keep in mind that there may be many repeaters all around the world linked to the reflector, and you will be keying the transmitter on all of them up when you transmit.  If you are going to do a long QSO and don\rquote t need to tie up all of the linked repeaters drop the link before starting so that your traffic stays local.\par
\par
5)      Observe normal repeater guidelines like allowing stations to break in if you are on an extended QSO.\par
