\par
\b So, How Does This \ldblquote Linking\rdblquote  Thing Work?   \b0  \par
\par
Example:  If you want to link the VHF repeater to reflector REF030B follow these steps: \par
\par
1)      Listen first to be sure no one is using the repeater.\par
\par
2)      If no one is transmitting put your radio on channel PLDDV, give your call sign and announce that you are going to link the repeater to a reflector (give the name of the reflector you are linking to).\par
\par
3)      Put your radio on channel PLDDVINF and key the mic for 1 to 2 seconds to check the current link status.   The repeater should respond telling you either that the repeater is linked or that it is not currently linked.\par
\par
4)      If the repeater is not currently linked go to step 6\par
\par
5)      If the repeater is linked put the radio on channel PLDDVUNL and key for 1 to 2 seconds to drop the link.  The repeater should respond telling you that the system is not currently linked.\par
\par
6)      Put the radio on channel PLDDV30B and key for 1 to 2 seconds to link to REF030B.  The repeater should respond with \ldblquote remote system linked\rdblquote .\par
\par
7)      Put the radio back on PLDDV after it is linked to begin your QSO.\par
